In order to start up email, simply type "mutt" into the command line.
This will open up mutt and allow you to view your emails. If you click "m", you will be able to draft and send an email. 
First, enter the sender address. Press Enter
Next, enter the subject. Press Enter.
Next, type your message. If you are in Vim, press "i" to begin to type, press "esc" and then ":wq" to save your message.
Next, press "y" to send your email.
